


Dear Bitstream Exchange & Video Conformance Adhoc Group members, 

Matsushita Conformance Bitstream No:17 (Long Sequence 0-60 frames)
---------------------------------------
MEI.stream17.long is a bitstream containing the concatenation of two bitstreams
of different sizes and bitrates.   

The following are detail
description of the bitstream :

Sequence 1
----------
a) flower garden at CCIR size.
b) size : CCIR 601 (704x480)
c) bitrate : 4 Mbps
d) number of frame : 61
e) frame structure : IBBP frame coding
f) decoded picture file : firstseq.image.long

Sequence 2
----------
a) football 
b) size : 256x256
c) bitrate : 2 Mbps
d) number of frame : 61
e) frame structure : IBBP frame coding
f) decoded picture file : secondseq.image.long

Sequence 1 is followed by sequence 2, with a sequence_end_code in between
the sequences.  
vbv_delay value is inserted in sequence 2 assuming the bit rate of sequence 2.

Your decoding results and comments for the bitstream will be very
much appreciated.

Thank you very much.


Best Regards

Siew-Tan Chong

AV/Information Research Centre
Asia Matsushita Electric (S) Pte Ltd
Singapore
Email : stchong@avirc.ams.com.sg



------------------------- Specification of 17 ---------------------------------
Bitstream:          17
Title:              Concatenated sequences of different picture sizes with 
                    VBV continuity.
Profile and Level:  MP@ML of differing sampling dimensions and bitrates 
                    for each of the N concatenated sequences.
Description:        Concatenated sequences of different picture sizes with 
                    VBV continuity
Functional stage:   controller
Purpose:            Realistic decoders will encounter concatenated sequences 
                    where each sequenece will possess different bitstream 
                    parameters (frame dimensions and rates).
Parameters:         2*4 and 2*60 frames
Organization:       Hitachi & Matsushita
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The format of the decoded pictures is as usual:
        First Sequence :
        ================
        4:2:0 frame ("display" order) 8 bits/component
        width : 704 pels/line
        height :  480 lines/frame
 
                      width              
                +---------------+       
                |               |          
                |      Y0       | height
                |               |
                | width/2       |
                +-------+-------+
                |  Cb0  | 
                |       | height/2
                +-------+
                |  Cr0  | height/2
                |       |
                +-------+-------+        
                |               |
                |      Y1       |
                |               |        
                |               |        
                +-------+-------+ 
                |       |


        Second Sequence :
        ================
        4:2:0 frame ("display" order) 8 bits/component
        width : 256 pels/line
        height :  256 lines/frame
 
                      width              
                +---------------+       
                |               |          
                |      Y0       | height
                |               |
                | width/2       |
                +-------+-------+
                |  Cb0  | 
                |       | height/2
                +-------+
                |  Cr0  | height/2
                |       |
                +-------+-------+        
                |               |
                |      Y1       |
                |               |        
                |               |        
                +-------+-------+ 
                |       |
 
 

--------------------------- end of readme ---------------------------------
